      • hasDuplicatesShouldReturnTrueWhenClassNameIsDuplicateButBytecodeDiffers

        public void hasDuplicatesShouldReturnTrueWhenClassNameIsDuplicateButBytecodeDiffers()
                                                                             throws Exception
        This test compares two files with the same exact relative path (so they look like the same file) but they exist in two different folders and their bytecode doesn't match. This should be considered a duplicate. We set the test up so it fails if it finds the same class name/path twice (meaning, it does not compare bytecode).
        Throws:
        Exception

      • hasDuplicatesShouldReturnFalseWhenClassNameIsDuplicateAndBytecodeDiffers

        public void hasDuplicatesShouldReturnFalseWhenClassNameIsDuplicateAndBytecodeDiffers()
                                                                              throws Exception
        This test compares two files with the same exact relative path (so they look like the same file) but they exist in two different folders and their bytecode doesn't match. This should be considered a duplicate. We set the test up so it finds duplicates only if the bytecode differs.
        Throws:
        Exception

      • toOutputStringOutputsTwoArtifactsWhereBytecodeIsExactMatch

        public void toOutputStringOutputsTwoArtifactsWhereBytecodeIsExactMatch()
                                                                throws Exception
        Verify the output string contains all the information, specifically, it should list which artifacts were an exact match (meaning, the bytecode of the .class files were identical). This helps users determine which artifacts they can ignore when fix the BanDuplicateClasses error.
        Throws:
        Exception

      • toOutputStringOutputsFourArtifactsWhereBytecodeIsExactMatchInTwoAndExactMatchInOtherTwo

        public void toOutputStringOutputsFourArtifactsWhereBytecodeIsExactMatchInTwoAndExactMatchInOtherTwo()
                                                                                             throws Exception
        This verifies the output string contains all the information, specifically, it should list which artifacts were an exact match. In this case we have 4 artifacts: 1, 2, 3, and 4. The bytecode of 1 and 2 match each other, the bytecode of 3 and 4 match each other, but 1 and 2 don't match 3 and 4.
        Throws:
        Exception
